Description: Panoro Energy ASA is a Norway-based independent exploration and production (E&P) company. The Company holds production, development, and exploration assets in West and North Africa. Operations in West Africa include Block G consisting of the Okume Complex and Ceiba Field in Equatorial Guinea, the Dussafu License offshore southern Gabon and OML 113 offshore western Nigeria, which is classified as held for sale. The North African portfolio comprises a participating interest in five oil field concessions (TPS), the Sfax Offshore Exploration Permit (SOEP), and the Ras El Besh concession, all in the region of the city of Sfax, Tunisia. The Company maintains its registered address in Oslo with offices in London (headquarters), Malabo and Tunis.
